The prison museum in Deer Lodge Montana has a large car museum also.. they 
have a bus, a beetle, a dune buggy like mad max... i think there was a ghia 
there... and ... a T ford with the original side tent for camping with..
http://www.pcmaf.org/auto.htm 

it was worth the visit! 

Detroit has the automotive hall of fame, that isn't really for cars.. but 
more for the people... there 2 cars in the building.. one is a 67? Beetle
http://www.automotivehalloffame.org/visit.php 

If you go next door to the Henry Ford Museum.. there is a early bus camper 
among others.. dune buggy, and early beetle too.
http://www.hfmgv.org/ 

There is a auto museum in Nebraska.. I can't find the name ... 

Las Vegas Has the Imperial Palace Casino and Car museum... with an early bus 
http://www.imperialpalace.com/autos.php 


